DURBAN - The P7-2 (M70) known as Edendale Road toward KwaGezubuso in Pietermaritzburg has been closed due to recent storm damage that resulted in severe cracks that pose a risk to road users.The KZN Department of Transport said the road would be reopened once all repairs were completed.“Kindly be informed that P7-2 (M70) Edendale Road toward KwaGezubuso will be closed today until the section is repaired. Users will use deviations that the team is currently opening in the area,” said the department in a statement yesterday.Msunduzi Municipality said the deputy mayor and chairperson of the Infrastructure Services Committee, Mxolisi Mkhize, visited Edendale Road yesterday to ensure a speedy response to the road damage following the recent hailstorm in the city.The municipality said the department’s staff were already on site and preparations were being made for alternative routes to be used while repairs were conducted.MORE ON THISMillions of rand in storm damage in Howick with the possibility of the figure rising as damage is calculatedKZN farmers sufferers over R50 million in damages due to stormsZikalala calls for declaration of State of Disaster in KZN following recent storm damage which will cost R3.3bn to repairKZN Premier Zikalala to visit schools to assess readiness ahead of the start of the academic yearWATCH: All schools will open despite 186 schools damaged by recent storms, says KZN Department of Education"We thank the department for responding swiftly on this matter and we are urging road users to make use of alternative routes and to exercise patience as the safety of motorists and pedestrians remains the priority,“ Mkhize said.Mkhize urged all those who use Selby Msimang Road towards KwaGezubuso to use the alternative routes, adding that pedestrians should refrain from walking on this road until the repairs were completed.Msunduzi Municipality deputy mayor and chairperson of the Infrastructure Services Committee,  Mxolisi Mkhize, visited the M70 known as Edendale Road today after it was closed for repairs due to recent storm damage. Picture: Supplied.Msunduzi Municipality deputy mayor and chairperson of the Infrastructure Services Committee,  Mxolisi Mkhize, visited the M70 known as Edendale Road today after it was closed for repairs due to recent storm damage. Picture: Supplied.The M70 known as Edendale Road was closed for repairs due to recent storm damage. Picture: Supplied by KZN Transport.Msunduzi Municipality deputy mayor and chairperson of the Infrastructure Services Committee,  Mxolisi Mkhize, visited the M70 known as Edendale Road today after it was closed for repairs due to recent storm damage. Picture: Supplied.THE MERCURY